				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Young Bards Today(cont)<a name="6503"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 19 03 4:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I hate doing threads like this, but the other one was kinda getting long and I didnt know if anyone would see a post on it...
<br />

<br />

<br />
Little background first... Started eq about 2 years ago and got a warrior up to lvl 18, stopped playing do to summer connection.  Started back up about a month ago when I was talking to a couple of friends and thy had told me alot of stuff had changed since I played (AA's PoP books)
<br />

<br />
I started back in and got some help from a good friend with a 63 wizzy.  Since then played about every class trying to find one I enjoyed.  I finally settled with a bard, there is just something about them... the speed, always busy, always needed, abillity to solo.. anyways.
<br />

<br />
I hit lvl 22 this morning, spending the last 4 lvls in the Paludal Caverns.  During that time I would twist regen, haste, and slow and melee.   At times I seemed really busy and trying to target mobs and attacking them would cause me to skip in my twisting at times...
<br />

<br />
More so I'm wondering when is it good to just twist and not worry about melee? Or should I try and keep twisting 3 song and melee?  
<br />

<br />
I know there is so many options that I can do(aka the bard life)  I just want to try and be the most effective.... 
<br />

<br />
Thanks</span></td>
