				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Young Bards Today(cont)<a name="6504"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 19 03 4:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In my opinion, and I am sure there are other opinions of what a bard should be doing, I believe that a bard should never just sit back and not melee. I always keep my songs twisting while I melee, and when there are no mobs I keep my chorus of replenishment going for mana regen.
<br />

<br />
How are you trying to target the mobs? If there is a MA are you using an assist hotbutton? That might make things easier. My assist button is always number 7 for me so I can quickly hit 7 while twisting and not skip my songs too much. If you are not using a MA, are you clicking at the mobs with your mouse? If you are, maybe you could try using F8 instead. It will target the nearest mob to you.
<br />

<br />
I have a lvl 61 bard and I always twist 4 songs at a time when grouping or soloing. The only time I ever slack off is when I am grouped with friends and we are just fooling around.
<br />

<br />
I fully believe a bards role includes both effective twisting and meleeing. Bard meleeing can be pretty impressive with the right songs playing  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /> I hit for 80's and 90's pretty regularly. Being the most effective to me would be providing more melee damage help while providing the songs to enhance the attack.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
