				<td colspan="2"><span>If Im in a melee heavy group.. I use hastes as my primary twists.. and i melee as well... with mana during down time... 
<br />

<br />
If Im in a melee light group.. I will usually switch to drums/dots.  I can do more DPS with drums/dots then wth weapons.. and since we are lacking in melee my haste songs are really not effective in this group setting (IMHO)... 
<br />

<br />
I think what you will learn Fannon, is;
<br />

<br />
1.   There is no pat answer to the question &quot;when is it good to just twist and not worry about melee?&quot;
<br />

<br />
and
<br />

<br />
2.  Bards are flexable enough to be able switch roles depending on the group make up/mob.</span></td>
