				<td colspan="2"><span>Let me start by saying, my bard was not my main till he dinged 54 and a few AA's and passed my monk, so he hunted in all the &quot;spots&quot;, including paludal.
<br />

<br />
Being that I had a twink lute with a 2.4 mod at the time, I found that I could equip my lute, sing AoE slow, regen, and haste, and have NO other healers in the group, and no one ever lost health, ever.  It was the only time I consistantly exp'd in a group w/o melee'ing.
<br />

<br />
If you are in paludal, at that level, in that zone, a bard can be main and only healer in a group, so using a lute is a better idea than melee'ing.  Once you hit 25-26, and head to a new zone, such as highkeep, you will not be able to keep up with the amount of HP the group members lose, and you will need to find a healer, and you should then melee.  Using only a lute in paludal is not only ok, its recommended, imo.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
