				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Young Bards Today(cont)<a name="6796"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 28 03 3:50 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>For the most part I completely agree with the previous statements.  There are only two situations that I can think of right now where I do not melee.  The first involves kiting with a ranger friend of mine when niether of us is up to meleeing. (We root and dot the mobs to death) but the far more prevelant is in a group when I am in charge of CC.  Karnor's Castle is a good example of a place where I generally stay away from meleeing.  In that case I generally stay back and twist whatever songs I have decided will help the best while keeping an eye out for adds.  In places like Karnor's where adds come often, I find I am much quicker to pick them off when I don't have a mob filling my screen.  Still you will get a feel for different situations and change your tactics accordingly.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
