				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Young Bards Today(cont)<a name="6804"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 28 03 9:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Now that I've reached my 50's I've found more and more that my role as a melee bard decreases (or at least my impact on DPS).  More often than not I fill the role of an enchanter in the group: Mezzing adds, hasting, slowing, charming, etc.  Sure, everyone knows bards can do it, and I practiced this while soloing, but in my 50's I find people rely on these skills more than when I was pre 50.
<br />

<br />
When I was low level, people would commend me on being able to twist 3 songs effectively, and nearly 4 songs with only short dropoffs between songs, so if I messed up the twist or dropped a song for a round, many people wouldn't mind... in fact, very few folks notice. As long as folks 'feel' like their hasted, or 'feel' like the mobs are slowed, I normally don't hear a peep out of folks for what I was twisting.  As the levels and stakes got higher, folks would have special requests for a song here or there, and these days, specific roles for me.
<br />

<br />
When I enter a group, they usually tell me (or I'll ask) and they'll tell me: All haste/melee buff songs or Poor Man's Enchanter, or what have you.  It's been an interesting road, and I find that the more input folks have for requests, the more I learn.  Just last night I was the dispeller for Damage Shields in SG, something I had never twisted before.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
