				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Young Bards Today(cont)<a name="7237"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 13 03 2:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am a 59 bard on the Seventh Hammer and have my bard as my main with various alts played for relaxation.  I have always been a melee bard and have only even met someone once that was a pure support bard (ie only played instruments).  I cannot even fathom how boring that is and how much waste there is of the extra DPS.  At 59, I dual weild my epic and a defenders lightblade, only have 10 AA (1 point into Crit) but I hit with epic for over 90 in off hand and Defenders Lightblade up to 128 without Crit.  I hit for 218 as the highest melee crit so far.  I always have 3 songs going for group, 4 if I have to mezz and am not including selos or any of the other long duration songs.  I contribute a ton to the DPS aside from the fact that you have to melee to get the epic proc which is the 55% group haste, 30 attack boost, and 30 Str with its additional attack bonus.  It is nice to use epic proc and stack a few haste songs onto it with a slow on the mob or Cantata for mana/regen.  Standing back and just playing makes for a prettu useless bard imo and any bard that cannot handle basic crowd control while melee'ing needs to reconsider their class.  Why would melee prevent you from doing the same songs as you can just standing there (other than 5 or more mobs... best to run here anyway...)?  EQ allows you to change view so you can always take a back view or side view for mezzing the mobs while meleeing the one in front of you.
<br />
The only time I do not melee in a group is while I am root-rotting a mob with a dotting class or if the group has pulled so large a train that all you can do is continuously switch targets for mezzing and cannot afford to hit a mob and wake it up.  Bards are the masters of bringing up any area of the group that is lacking and can always provide some additional DPS meleeing at the same time.  If you think that the instument bonus is better than pure melee than feel free to swap between weapons and instruments while stringing and then you get the best of both worlds.  Flexibility is what make the bards so powerful a class.  Even at a young age, when bards melee skills are kind of weak, there are always weapons with nice procs to bring up the DPS or help in a fight... the epic is not the only reason to melee.  I can use Orb of Tishan to debuss MR or a Harmonic Dagger to stun or Venomous Axe with its 85DD proc.... bards are sweet melee class.</span></td>
