				<td colspan="2"><span>My point is that a bard can do both the melee and twisting in the songs... even with instruments thrown in.  Getting good instruments now-a-days is very easy and very cheap to do.  Walrus skin drums are the next best under Selo's Drums of the March and can be bought for 500 pp frequently... They smoke the MMBD and the only worthwhile upgrade from them is the Drums of the Beast.  Good Magic Wind Instruments are also very cheap to buy like the Flute of Eternal Night and getting an Orcish Lute of Singing is also very easy until you can get Kelin's Seven Stringed Lute from Plane of Hate.  McVaxius Horn of War is very cheap now or the higher bards can just use the Instrument Weapons if they do not have their epic yet.  There is no reason for a bard to not melee with the excuss of twisting songs unless they are very uncoordinated... in which case, bard is the wrong class to be playing.  Only encounters that melee should be flat avoided is in the case of Epic Mob encounters such as dragons where the bard is solely there to do resists and Occlusion of Sound and NOT get agro at all if can be helped or as listed before.</span></td>
